Type: viral infection.
Cause: Hepatitis viruses, alcohol abuse and autoimmunity.
Symptoms: inflammation of the liver, abdominal pain, loss of appetite, fatigue, dark urine, pale stool and jaundice.
Incubation period: hepatitis a (15-50) days, hepatitis b (60-150) days, hepatitis c (14-182) days.
Prevention: Safer sex practices, including minimizing the number of partners and using barrier protective measures, Harm reduction practices for injecting drug users, Safe food and water.